# Security

## AuthN / AuthZ (how we do it here)

- Guards: `JwtAuthGuard`, `OptionalJwtAuthGuard`, `RolesGuard` + `@Roles('COMMERCE_ADMIN', …)`.
- Authorize in the **service/use-case**, not only by hiding UI.
- Resource access: load by id **and** verify `userId` / ownership / role. Ignore client-supplied owner ids.

```typescript
// ❌ IDOR — trust body
await prisma.order.findFirst({ where: { id: body.orderId } });

// ✅ scope to actor (or elevated role path)
await prisma.order.findFirst({ where: { id: orderId, userId: user.id } });
```

Roles in play: Customer, Commerce Admin, Content Admin, Writer, SEO Editor, Medical Reviewer, Creator, Brand, Finance, Support, Super Admin. No convenience “god” role.

Rate-limit auth + sensitive POSTs (checkout, payout, publish, award). Session cookies: httpOnly + Secure when used; CSRF strategy must match transport.

## Input / uploads

- Every external input through Zod (`ZodValidationPipe` / shared schemas).
- Prisma only (parameterized). No string-concat SQL.
- Uploads: MIME + size; no executable inline; private objects via **signed URLs**.

## Secrets & PII

- Never commit `.env` / keys / dumps.
- Never log tokens, passwords, OTPs, PAN/CVV, raw provider payloads.
- Cards: provider tokens only. Mask PII in logs; audit admin PII reads.

## Privileged + payments

Audit: publish, award, payout, refund, role-change, finance.  
Payments must not report success on unknown/partial provider state. Webhook handlers **idempotent** (`eventId` / `idempotencyKey`).
